genresAdvancedInfo.name: libyan hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Libyan hip hop is a subgenre of hip hop music that originated in Libya and is influenced by traditional Libyan music and culture. It often incorporates Arabic lyrics and rhythms, as well as elements of Western hip hop. The lyrics often address social and political issues in Libya and the wider Arab world.
